OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1777269939
OL,3,CCampbell likens Starmer to Bush as he
OL,4,Cwarns of 'dark place' if Labour fails
OL,6,F"George W Bush was somebody who if he
OL,7,Fwas there now sitting on that sofa
OL,8,Fchatting to you, you would think, what
OL,9,Fa charming, funny guy. And why has he
OL,10,Fgot this reputation of being stupid,
OL,11,Fbecause he's really clever?
OL,13,F"As soon as the cameras came on him,
OL,14,Fhe was a different being.
OL,16,F"And I sometimes feel like if you
OL,17,Fcould only see Keir in a kind of real
OL,18,Fhuman setting, he can be impressive,
OL,19,Fhe can be charming, be all the things
OL,20,Fthat you'd want a political leader to
OL,21,Fbe.
OL,26,@nD@AOUuD@AOUxD@AOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/6
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,309,300,200,140,000,100
PN,30804
SC,0004
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F308A1777269939
OL,3,CCampbell likens Starmer to Bush as he
OL,4,Cwarns of 'dark place' if Labour fails
OL,6,F"There's something about the mechanism
OL,7,Fof modern political communication that
OL,8,FI think sometimes stops him being
OL,9,Fhimself."
OL,11,FDespite Labour struggling in UK-wide
OL,12,Fpolls and Nigel Farage's Reform UK in
OL,13,Fthe ascendency, the former strategist
OL,14,F` who now presents a podcast ` said he
OL,15,Fwas "confident" it can be turned
OL,16,Faround.
OL,18,FBut he added: "If it isn't turned
OL,19,Faround, by the way, we are in deep
OL,20,Fshit.
OL,26,@nD@AOUqD@IO]wD@EOUwD@OO]zD@OOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G4/6
